  "text": "To overcome the limitations of OF there is a growing focus on feature based methods, such as SIFT [CITATION_1] . Such methods assume that feature points can be reliably detected and matched in both the image and the template so that there are enough potent matches to estimate a global transformation model, perhaps using RANSAC [CITATION_2] . Despite the large body of work in this field, the process can fail, especially if there are not enough distinct features in the template or the image. See Fig. 1 for illustrations.",
